column34:
Relating to the most profound freedoms, qualities, and happiness that modern society and culture have stripped away from us, The Ecstasy of Nothing is a spiritually inclined non-fiction philosophy book that rationally investigates language and concepts from a perspective never before advocated in this fashion - one that has impaired and imprisoned us as modern beings.

The author claims to have discovered and built upon a glaring truth in modern experience, one present now more than ever.

What is this truth? We are enslaved by the conceptual! While language and subsequently concepts have been our greatest invention or discovery, now, in the modern Western world, we have become its subordinate, its slave. We have lost connection with what he calls the Real, a simple but beautiful experience outside of the illusions and unrealities of modern life.

The Ecstasy of Nothing: A Philosophy of Language, Reality, And the Phenomenology of Modern Experience is a 60,000-word non-fiction philosophy-of-language book for those who are spiritually and philosophically inclined. Taking inspiration from Wittgenstein and Sartre, this book does three main things. Firstly, it offers new and relatable theories on ways language and concepts separate us from reality. Secondly, it offers a glance into the experience of the world without the chains of concepts and how we may go beyond new-age connotations of spirituality to properly and sensibly rejoice with beauty, art, and nature as modern beings. The third relates to action! What are we to do? From unique and nuanced criticisms of capitalism to how we approach each other and our lives, he advocates new ways to find our autonomous will in a conceptualised world characterised by our unfreedom, and from there, step by step, advocates a new form of anarchy.

column34: When her world turns upside down Aoife Brennan, Irishwoman, mother, marketeer and about to become bitcoin advocate, has to readjust, and learn to live again. How does this vibrant and sassy woman get on her feet again, date again, learn to love again? This is a roller coaster ride, funny in parts, poignant in parts, laugh out loud, cry maybe too. This is very Irish, very wonderful and full of hope. Her observations on life are sharp, her acute view of herself is painful in parts and also kind in parts and above all she is very human. And then there is bitcoin and blockchain ....The first novel in a trilogy that looks at being human and being blockchain in equal measure. And while it may be erotica it is more - it is as Irish as Jane Austin is English in its understanding of manners in Ireland. And then there is the sex. Oh and bitcoin.

column34:
The Price of Bliss Eternal is the first sci-fi novella ever written by philosopher Thomas Dylan Daniel. This is a story that chronicles the exploits of two scientists who make a world-changing discovery.

For Nils Osterhaut, it's a chance to be a part of history. For Eddie Moreno, it's an opportunity to explore an even stranger universe which emerges in the wake of his most remarkable achievement. However, these men have families which will forever be altered by the most remarkable discovery of either of their lives.

Imagine: what might be the price of bliss eternal? To live over and over, the happiest moment of your life, forever... is this a fantasy or a nightmare?

Stow's meta graphic novel/comic book series follows the adventures of HappyMan as he navigates his self-created universe on a quest to Worthy.

HappyMan begins his journey in a sketch pad, encountering surreal sidekicks and meta monsters on his quest to worthy. As he learns to create his own universe, he transitions to a rich, hi-res digital landscape, discovering new superpowers and upgrades along the way.

En este libro encontrars todo lo necesario para comprender a fondo la revolucin econmica del siglo XXI. El Bitcoin como moneda y protocolo. Las transacciones, los bloques, las cadenas, los mineros, etc. Todo te lo explico en estas pginas de una manera gil y sencilla.

El Bitcoin como moneda es la evolucin natural del dinero en la era digital. Soluciona mucho mejor los problemas que tiene que resolver el dinero. Te explicar todas y cada una de sus caractersticas enfrentndolas con el dinero FIAT. Pero no hay evolucin sin revolucin: el cambio que supone el Bitcoin se debe a que altera totalmente el paradigma de como funciona la economa actual (basada en deuda); Bitcoin nace para atajar esto y solucionarlo.

Pero si el Bitcoin en s es una revolucin, lo que ha provocado lo es an ms. Ha abierto un mundo de posibilidades gracias a la aplicacin de sus protocolos. Y debido al xito de su creacin, hoy en da existen ms criptomonedas y altcoins.

Finally the compendium you were waiting for. Everything you always wanted to know about Bitcoin but never quite understood.

In this book you will find everything you need to fully understand the economic revolution of the 21st century. Bitcoin as a currency and protocol. Transactions, blocks, chains, miners, etc. I explain everything to you in these pages in an agile and simple way.

Bitcoin as a currency is the natural evolution of money in the digital age. It solves much better the problems that money has to solve. I will explain each and every one of its characteristics facing them with FIAT money. column33: How Not To Be A Dick
column34:
"How Not to Be a Dick" cuts to the heart of how we men exist in the world. Using a combination of illustrations, personal narratives, and concepts from rational emotive therapy and cognitive behavioral therapy, I dig into the core challenges of male use of power.

The thesis is that POWER is always in play, but we can be conscious about distributing the COST of its use, and allowing for maximum autonomy of all parties.

Basically, it means not bullying people and being a dick, but the book provides insight into why even the "nicest" guys often flip and react with violence and aggression. It provides tools to help avoid these pitfalls.

This book is not intended to be a solution, but more of an opening for discussion around the harms we've caused and the harms we've withstood.

column34:
Relating to the most profound freedoms, qualities, and happiness that modern society and culture have stripped away from us, The Ecstasy of Nothing is a spiritually inclined non-fiction philosophy book that rationally investigates language and concepts from a perspective never before advocated in this fashion - one that has impaired and imprisoned us as modern beings.

The author claims to have discovered and built upon a glaring truth in modern experience, one present now more than ever.

What is this truth? We are enslaved by the conceptual! While language and subsequently concepts have been our greatest invention or discovery, now, in the modern Western world, we have become its subordinate, its slave. We have lost connection with what he calls the Real, a simple but beautiful experience outside of the illusions and unrealities of modern life.

The Ecstasy of Nothing: A Philosophy of Language, Reality, And the Phenomenology of Modern Experience is a 60,000-word non-fiction philosophy-of-language book for those who are spiritually and philosophically inclined. Taking inspiration from Wittgenstein and Sartre, this book does three main things. Firstly, it offers new and relatable theories on ways language and concepts separate us from reality. Secondly, it offers a glance into the experience of the world without the chains of concepts and how we may go beyond new-age connotations of spirituality to properly and sensibly rejoice with beauty, art, and nature as modern beings. The third relates to action! What are we to do? From unique and nuanced criticisms of capitalism to how we approach each other and our lives, he advocates new ways to find our autonomous will in a conceptualised world characterised by our unfreedom, and from there, step by step, advocates a new form of anarchy.

column33: How To Not Be A Dick
column34:
"How Not to Be a Dick" cuts to the heart of how we men exist in the world. Using a combination of illustrations, personal narratives, and concepts from rational emotive therapy and cognitive behavioral therapy, I dig into the core challenges of male use of power.

The thesis is that POWER is always in play, but we can be conscious about distributing the COST of its use, and allowing for maximum autonomy of all parties.

Basically, it means not bullying people and being a dick, but the book provides insight into why even the "nicest" guys often flip and react with violence and aggression. It provides tools to help avoid these pitfalls.

This book is not intended to be a solution, but more of an opening for discussion around the harms we've caused and the harms we've withstood.

column34:
Relating to the most profound freedoms, qualities, and happiness that modern society and culture have stripped away from us, The Ecstasy of Nothing is a spiritually inclined non-fiction philosophy book that rationally investigates language and concepts from a perspective never before advocated in this fashion - one that has impaired and imprisoned us as modern beings.

The author claims to have discovered and built upon a glaring truth in modern experience, one present now more than ever.

What is this truth? We are enslaved by the conceptual! While language and subsequently concepts have been our greatest invention or discovery, now, in the modern Western world, we have become its subordinate, its slave. We have lost connection with what he calls the Real, a simple but beautiful experience outside of the illusions and unrealities of modern life.

The Ecstasy of Nothing: A Philosophy of Language, Reality, And the Phenomenology of Modern Experience is a 60,000-word non-fiction philosophy-of-language book for those who are spiritually and philosophically inclined. Taking inspiration from Wittgenstein and Sartre, this book does three main things. Firstly, it offers new and relatable theories on ways language and concepts separate us from reality. Secondly, it offers a glance into the experience of the world without the chains of concepts and how we may go beyond new-age connotations of spirituality to properly and sensibly rejoice with beauty, art, and nature as modern beings. The third relates to action! What are we to do? From unique and nuanced criticisms of capitalism to how we approach each other and our lives, he advocates new ways to find our autonomous will in a conceptualised world characterised by our unfreedom, and from there, step by step, advocates a new form of anarchy.

column34: When her world turns upside down Aoife Brennan, Irishwoman, mother, marketeer and about to become bitcoin advocate, has to readjust, and learn to live again. How does this vibrant and sassy woman get on her feet again, date again, learn to love again? This is a roller coaster ride, funny in parts, poignant in parts, laugh out loud, cry maybe too. This is very Irish, very wonderful and full of hope. Her observations on life are sharp, her acute view of herself is painful in parts and also kind in parts and above all she is very human. And then there is bitcoin and blockchain ....The first novel in a trilogy that looks at being human and being blockchain in equal measure. And while it may be erotica it is more - it is as Irish as Jane Austin is English in its understanding of manners in Ireland. And then there is the sex. Oh and bitcoin.
